# Assignment!

Fill out the template *twice*, for two different ideas.

Then compare and contrast and select one as the idea you're leaning towards
working on for your project week.


# Ideas for data storytelling - Idea 1

## You

What do you care about?
Music and songwriting

What do you know about?
Chord progressions and genres

What decisions do you face?
What aspects should I compare. Which correletions should I invesetigate?

## Seven templates

Training Kit (https://learn.lambdaschool.com/ds/module/recedjanlbpqxic2r) explains the seven templates from Priceonomics.

Can you apply the templates to your topics? 

1. Geographic Variation
Yes - chord progression popularity by country

2. Trend related to the news
Yes - chord progressions by position in charts

3. Who does that?
Yes - demographics of chord progression/genre preference

4. Answering a question people care about
Yes - What is the most lucrative chord progression to use?

5. Valuable to businesses
Yes - record companies/advertisers could benefit.

6. What's the most popular?
Yes - most popular chord progression

7. Cost/Money rankings
Yes - same as #4

## Misconceptions

What misconceptions do people have about your topic?
People don't consider a link between chord progression and psychological (and other) effects of music.

## Examples

What data storytelling example inspires you?
n/a

Could you do a new hypothesis, for the same question?
n/a

Could you do a new question, for the same topic?
n/a

Could you do a new topic, with the same "style"?
n/a

## Data

Where could you search for data about your topic?
Billboard sites, chord progression sites

